    "For any face f ∈ F we let H f = v∈f H v and define an orthogonal projector B f on H f which annihilates the orthogonal complement of e∈f A e H f and acts on e∈f A e H f by inserting the regular element of C and using local relations to bring the diagram back into product form:B f = 1 D 2 a∈Irr C d a.",
    "(4)Here d a is the quantum dimension of the object a, and D 2 = a d 2 a.",
    "A precise definition will be given in Section 4.5 below.It was shown that B f is an orthogonal projector in [26, page 10].",
    "Moreover, all {B f } f ∈F commute with each other, as has been shown in [27,Proposition 5.14].",
    "This fact will follow from Lemma 4.5 below.The Levin-Wen Hamiltonian is the formal commuting projector HamiltonianH LW = - f ∈F B f.A state ω: A → C is a frustration free ground state of H LW if ω(B f) = 1 for all f ∈ F. The following Proposition has been proved in [28] (see section 2.3 and Theorem 4.8 of that paper):Proposition 2.1."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This fact will follow from Lemma 4.5 below.The Levin-Wen Hamiltonian is the formal commuting projector HamiltonianH LW = - f ∈F B f.A state ω: A → C is a frustration free ground state of H LW if ω(B f) = 1 for all f ∈ F. The following Proposition has been proved in [28] (see section 2.3 and Theorem 4.8 of that paper):Proposition 2.1."
